    "purpose": "Plausibility rails for the simulator's editable inputs (CTO review 2026-07-10 item 8). Per use case: min/typical/max for the volume input and the value driver(s). SOFT rails — the UI warns on out-of-band entries ('that's well outside the typical range') and never blocks. 'typical' MUST equal the archetype's committed illustrative default (pinned by test).",
    "provenance": "Editorial. These are order-of-magnitude plausibility bounds for the target buyer (a 500–5,000-person organisation), derived from the committed illustrative defaults — not benchmarks. The defaults themselves remain the archetype/config values; nothing here feeds the cost engine.",
    "haircut_note": "value_realisation_default_pct is the starting position of the Q4 realisation slider: the share of the entered value the verdict counts (not everyone uses it; not all saved time turns into output). Editorial default, user-overridable."
